Police are treating the death of a 34-year-old man in South Lanarkshire on Friday evening as murder.
Brian Cogan, from Wishaw, died in Margaret Gardens in Hamilton after a number of men gathered in a residential cul-de-sac and a disturbance broke out.
Police are reviewing CCTV footage of the incident t the rear of Margaret Gardens at about 19:20.
Detective chief inspector Gary Boyd said it was not yet clear what led to the victim's death. 
DCI Boyd appealed for witnesses and said: &quot;A young man has lost his life and it's imperative we know how, and why this happened and trace whoever is responsible.&quot;
